To install Graphical Environment You First Need To Install Network Manager by using sudo pacman -S networkmanager
After You install network manager you can install desktop environment you like gnome kde plasma etc
After You install Graphical Environment Install Firefox Or Konqueror
Firefox
sudo pacman -S firefox
Konqueror
sudo pacman -S konqueror
You Download Fallback Linux Logo On Readme In This Website https://github.com/Haikal02-alt/Fallback-Linux
Then Save The fallback linux On Browser By Click Save Image As Then If You See 543367371-e46b4a24-7c35-4013-afa6-99b4902334c7.png Change It To fallback-linux-logo.png Then Save it to Download
Then Open Terminal And Run sudo mv /home/yourusername/Downloads/fallback-linux-logo.png /usr/share/pixmaps/
Then sudo cp /usr/share/pixmaps/fallback-linux-logo.png /usr/share/pixmaps/archlinux-logo.png
Then sudo cp /usr/share/pixmaps/fallback-linux-logo.png /usr/share/pixmaps/archlinux-logo.svg
Then sudo cp /usr/share/pixmaps/fallback-linux-logo.png /usr/share/pixmaps/archlinux-logo-text.svg
Then sudo cp /usr/share/pixmaps/fallback-linux-logo.png /usr/share/pixmaps/archlinux-logo-text-dark.svg
Then sudo nano /etc/os-release Then Change LOGO=archlinux-logo to LOGO=/usr/share/pixmaps/fallback-linux-logo.png (FOR KDE PLASMA)
After You Install Kde Plasma You Install the konsole and dolphin
For Kde Plasma Go To System settings Then Notifications Then System Notifications Then Play A Sound On Login And Logout

Installing A Desktop Environments

Gnome
sudo pacman -S gnome-extra
KDE Plasma
sudo pacman -S plasma
Cinnamon
sudo pacman -S cinnamon
XFCE
sudo pacman -S xfce4
LXQt
sudo pacman -S lxqt
LXDE
sudo pacman -S lxde
MATE
sudo pacman -S mate mate-extra

Popular Tiling & Lightweight Window Managers

Hyprland (Wayland compositor)
sudo pacman -S hyprland
Sway (Wayland i3-like compositor)
sudo pacman -S sway
i3wm
sudo pacman -S i3-wm i3status dmenu
MangoWM (community/AUR, not in official repos)  
Install via AUR helper (e.g., yay)
yay -S mangowm
IceWM
sudo pacman -S icewm

Display Manager
SDDM
sudo pacman -S sddm
sudo systemctl enable sddm
GDM3
sudo pacman -S gdm
sudo systemctl enable gdm
LightDM
sudo pacman -S lightdm lightdm-gtk-greeter
sudo systemctl enable lightdm

Manual Start
XFCE
exec startxfce4
GNOME
exec gnome-session
Then Run
startx
